<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO SERIES - INSTALL - GEAR SHIFT LEVER</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>GEAR SHIFT LEVER</title>
        <para>Remote control housings are installed the same way as gear shift levers.</para>
        <para>For standard and forward shift bar housings, make sure the two (2) balls and tension springs are in the
            shift bar housing top bores.
        </para>
        <para>Make sure the shift block and yoke notches are aligned in the neutral position.</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position a new gear shift lever gasket on the gear shift lever mounting surface (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017p7">Figure 257</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017p7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017p7" filename="../figg13/G13017P7.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 257. Gear Shift Lever Into Shift Block</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fit the gear shift lever into the shift block (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017p7">Figure 257</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Eaton/Fuller Sealant #71205 or Loctite 242 to the retaining bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the retaining bolts and tighten to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#8226;m) of torque (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017p8">Figure 258</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017p8" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017p8" filename="../figg13/G13017P8.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 258. Install Retaining Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
